      • stepsOrderedBy

        public Iterable<Pair<Step<?>,​Float>> stepsOrderedBy​(Key stat,
                                                          boolean trueForAscending)
        Parameters:
        stat - statistics Key.
        trueForAscending - true for ordering by ascending, otherwise descending.
        Returns:
        the steps ordered by the long value representation of the given stat accompanied a factor by how it compares to the next value, where a value close to 1.0 signals them being close to equal, and a value of for example 0.5 signals that the value of the current step is half that of the next step.
